# Project: Memo (Stemo) — Audio Organization App

## Goal
Local-first, Kanban-style audio manager to move voice memos to finished songs.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vite + React + TypeScript PWA
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Storage)
- Offline: Dexie.js (IndexedDB) + Service Worker
- Sync: Outbox pattern, flush on `online` + Background Sync fallback
- DnD: @dnd-kit/core + @dnd-kit/sortable

## Design System (merged)
- Landing: charcoal `#0d0d0e`, lime `#c8ff57`, Instrument Serif + Bricolage Grotesque + DM Mono
- In-app audio UI: mint `#00FF9D` for play buttons, waveforms, speed controls

## Architecture Rules
- UI NEVER calls Supabase directly — use `src/db/repositories/*`
- All mutations write to Dexie first, then enqueue `syncQueue`
- Audio blobs stored locally in IndexedDB; upload to Storage on sync
- No native recording — file import only

## MVP Columns
Inbox → Ideas → Demos → Finished

## Audio Player
- Speed: 1x, 1.5x, 2x via `playbackRate`
- Continuous column playback: auto-advance to next song in column on `ended`

## Mobile
- `overscroll-behavior: none`, fixed AppShell header, touch-friendly dnd-kit sensors
